                        <p
                          id="fs-idp50313008"
                        >There is no change in mass number or atomic number during the emission of a γ ray unless the γ emission accompanies one of the other modes of decay.</p>
                        <p id="fs-idp18009856">
                          <span data-type="term" group-by="P" id="[redacted for uniqueness]">
                            Positron emission (β
                            <sup>+</sup> decay
                          </span>) is the emission of a positron from the nucleus. Oxygen-15 is an example of a nuclide that undergoes positron emission:
