                        <p id="fs-idp61393104">
                          where
                          <em data-effect="italics">N</em>
                          <sub>0</sub> is the initial number of nuclei or moles of the isotope, and
                          <em data-effect="italics">
                            N
                            <sub>t</sub>
                          </em> is the number of nuclei/moles remaining at time
                          <em data-effect="italics">t</em>.
                          <a
                            class="autogenerated-content"
                            href="#fs-idp79391408"
                          >Example 21.5</a> applies these calculations to find the rates of radioactive decay for specific nuclides.
                        </p>
